txt.en: Dómárr is at his camp in the Great Hall of Durin.\n\nDómárr will be pleased to hear the Durub captains have been defeated and the tribe's organization has been broken.
You have discovered Gazatu-ru, a camp of strangely organized Durub Orcs. They must have strong leaders to have such powerful delusions about their own grandeur.
'Good news, indeed!\n\n'Thank you [placeholder]. This blow will leave them quite vulnerable.'
Giving the Durub a Good Drubbing
You have discovered Gazatu-ru, a camp of strangely organized Durub Orcs. They must have strong leaders to have such powerful delusions about their own grandeur.

The Durub captains are at Gazatu-ru at the Great Hall of Durin, south of the Twenty-first Hall.\n\nYou should defeat the Durub captains, as they are responsible for the strong organization of the Orcs of Gazatu-ru.
